[{"_id":"7a938c53-6f09-3640-8191-8c0941e33c33","authorName":"Autostorage","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"","message":"Thank you for useful information! Was looking for a guide on optimal timeouts for a long time.","postId":"2009_05_error-handling-dd64acf2-8f2e-3f79-826f-43e4b6bae3c3","replyTo":"","date":"2009-06-13T20:31:55Z","timestamp":1244925115,"authorUserId":""},{"_id":"250a1d77-49ef-3a45-a0e4-5874be62227b","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"ad2250182ff26a84dda974e50cd94382","message":"@flatplanet: It \"hangs\" because it is waiting for the rest of the data to arrive.  \r\n\r\nYou could add a timer, so that the entire message would have to arrive within a certain time after the length prefix arrives. The length prefix example code has a maximum message size, but no timer.  \r\n\r\nOf course, the best way to avoid it is to fix the other side so that it sends valid data. :)","postId":"2009_05_error-handling-dd64acf2-8f2e-3f79-826f-43e4b6bae3c3","replyTo":"","date":"2009-08-05T16:35:16Z","timestamp":1249490116,"authorUserId":""},{"_id":"8c957c62-12f9-3382-b488-a0a7942c8003","authorName":"flatplanet","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"","message":"Why on Windows 2008 (r2) on reading packet without valid structure (lenght prefix + data) system don't throw Out Of Memory exception and system will hangs? Is a way to avid this?","postId":"2009_05_error-handling-dd64acf2-8f2e-3f79-826f-43e4b6bae3c3","replyTo":"","date":"2009-08-05T13:38:26Z","timestamp":1249479506,"authorUserId":""},{"_id":"1bc1c5d6-71ae-3313-a026-f1cfbc4d382e","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"ad2250182ff26a84dda974e50cd94382","message":"You should Close it and create a new one IMO. It *might* work to reuse the same instance, but AFAIK it's not guaranteed; the standard error handling response for any kind of error is to immediately Close the socket, and I would apply that same logic to the connecting socket.","postId":"2009_05_error-handling-dd64acf2-8f2e-3f79-826f-43e4b6bae3c3","replyTo":"c43043d0-86cf-3f79-aed6-0780c8c35d68","date":"2014-08-13T15:42:11Z","timestamp":1407944531,"authorUserId":"disqus:stephen_cleary"},{"_id":"c43043d0-86cf-3f79-aed6-0780c8c35d68","authorName":"Guillaume","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"3728e6f4a8b547f08329628b1320b3e2","message":"This seems like a mandatory complement to the MSDN documentation. I have a question about SocketError.TimedOut. Can I then retry with the same Socket instance (using BeginConnect) or should I preferably Close it and create a new one?\r\n\r\nThanks very much","postId":"2009_05_error-handling-dd64acf2-8f2e-3f79-826f-43e4b6bae3c3","replyTo":"","date":"2014-08-13T15:36:57Z","timestamp":1407944217,"authorUserId":""}]